LEXIFLOW TECHNOLOGIES INC - MEDICAL RECORD REVIEW CHECKLIST
=========================================================
For Personal Injury & Medical Malpractice Paralegals

PHASE 1: DOCUMENT ACQUISITION & ORGANIZATION
[ ] Cross-reference all providers in intake notes with HIPAA authorizations.
[ ] Verify that all facility records include:
    [ ] ER records / Triage notes
    [ ] Admission/Discharge summaries
    [ ] Operative reports
    [ ] Imaging reports (Radiology)
    [ ] Lab results
[ ] Ensure billing statements are requested separately if not in medical chart.
[ ] Sort records chronologically (Earliest date first).

PHASE 2: INITIAL DATA EXTRACTION
[ ] Identify Date of Incident (DOI) and first date of treatment.
[ ] Identify all diagnosing physicians and their specialties.
[ ] Flag any mention of pre-existing injuries or chronic conditions.
[ ] List all imaging (X-Ray, CT, MRI, EMG) and results.
[ ] Identify any gaps in treatment (30+ days).

PHASE 3: DETAILED MERIT REVIEW
[ ] Check for consistency between subjective complaints and objective findings.
[ ] Verify if treatment plan matches the diagnosis (Standard of Care).
[ ] Flag any "failed conservative treatment" (e.g. PT didn't help).
[ ] Note any recommendations for future care (Future Meds).
[ ] For MedMal: Identify specific deviations from hospital protocol.

PHASE 4: CHRONOLOGY & SPECIALS PREPARATION
[ ] Build comprehensive timeline of all encounters.
[ ] Extract specific billing charges for each date of service.
[ ] Verify insurance adjustments vs. total billed amounts.
[ ] Prepare "Key Findings" summary for attorney review.
[ ] Identify potential expert witness needs (e.g. Neuroradiologist).

